
[1]talus

   TA'LUS, n. [L. talus, the ankle.] In anatomy, the astragalus, or that
   bone of the foot which is articulated to the leg.

   1. In architecture, a slope; the inclination of any work.

   2. In fortification, the slope of a work, as a bastion, rampart or
   parapet.
